race.comment: CARRAMAR (5) debuted seven weeks ago when he finished ninth over 1200m at Wodonga, beaten 5 lengths. Likely improver who is worth another chance. BLUE CATTLE DOG (1) raced below his best last time when sixth over 1200m at Nowra. Well placed to turn things around in this easier race. ROYCROFTS COURAGE (2) was only fair on debut at Echuca but has trialled strongly at Corowa in readiness for his return to racing. The inside draw is a big tick for him and it wouldn't surprise to see him put his best foot forward. TRADER'S GUESS (10) won a recent trial at Corowa and showed good ability in his two heats in Victoria. Can play a leading role.
